The '''Church of All Souls''' is located on Every Street in [[Ancoats]], Manchester, England. It was designed by [[William Haley (architect)|William Haley]], and was constructed around 1839-1840 in a Romanesque style, from brown brick with stone dressing. It was built for Dr Samuel Warren. It has been a Grade II listed building since 15 October 1984.<ref name="listedbuilding" /> The church closed in 1984, and the building was subsequently used as a joinery workshop. It is now used by the '''Manchester Miracle Centre'''.<ref name="muc" />

